Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.45,0:00:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.41,0:00:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.73,0:00:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.82,0:00:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.93,0:00:34.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.94,0:00:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.33,0:00:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.60,0:00:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.74,0:00:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.92,0:01:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.98,0:01:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.10,0:01:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Exodia Necross"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.81,0:01:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He counter-attacks with Dragon Sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.13,0:01:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was one of the\N fights from Battle City...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.64,0:01:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Without even realizing it, I was lost in a sea of memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.24,0:01:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You got me, Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.04,0:01:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now just you wait, Gozaburo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll make you open an exit, even if I have to get rough!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.76,0:02:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our road of battle won't end in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.80,0:02:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! So Noah tricked us in the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.19,0:02:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got the best of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, we still don't really know that yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mokuba's gone, too!\N He probably got kidnapped by the jerk again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.80,0:02:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Noah stole Mokuba's body and escaped to the Real World.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.86,0:02:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.32,0:02:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.75,0:02:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What do you think, Other Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.59,0:02:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sorry. I just don't think the others are ready to forgive Noah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Partner, I get that you want to believe in Noah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.79,0:03:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But regardless, Noah went way too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.36,0:03:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}OTOGI!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.73,0:03:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}SHIZUKA!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.13,0:03:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yu... gi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.85,0:03:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know you want everyone to trust Noah, but it's too difficult for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.15,0:03:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.62,0:03:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s gone, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.71,0:03:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0} may be with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.55,0:03:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's certainly possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.43,0:03:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's just search for Noah. Otherwise we won't get out of this Virtual World.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.91,0:03:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OOH-OOH-AH! I'm starting to oohk like a moonkey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.87,0:03:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry oohp and find him, OOH-AH!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.59,0:03:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not good. Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s starting to talk even more like a monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to hurry up and find Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.42,0:04:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell is going on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuka!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.95,0:04:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Curse of Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.76,0:04:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell Flame!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.45,0:04:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Axe Raider!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.78,0:05:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Switching to Program File M2A5.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.17,0:05:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Changing missile target to floating mobile fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.18,0:05:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto, I'll use a missile to blow you from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.32,0:05:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with Yugi... and Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto... {\i1}I'll{\i0} have the last laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not {\i1}you{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.98,0:05:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good of you to come, Seto.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.49,0:06:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting to have a {\i1}nice{\i0}, {\i1}long{\i0} chat with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.37,0:06:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph. Don't make me {\i1}laugh{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.55,0:06:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.64,0:06:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got {\i1}plenty{\i0} of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.89,0:06:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we had a {\i1}hundred years{\i0} to sit and chat, I would only have one thing to say to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.08,0:06:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us return to the Real World at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.55,0:06:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, it's been some time since we used a game to settle one of our disputes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the time I took you on as my adopted son.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.92,0:06:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you lost to me as a {\i1}child{\i0}, what makes you think you can beat me in Chess {\i1}now{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.32,0:07:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really think I would go all out on a small child?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little berating of yourself to try and deny your loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.47,0:07:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.93,0:07:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we won't be playing Chess this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.64,0:07:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.70,0:07:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? I'm saying that I'll be playing you in the game you're best at.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.88,0:07:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard. So you're trying to get revenge for your defeat back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.60,0:07:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd been planning everything {\i1}since{\i0} then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.24,0:07:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Planning to steal Kaiba Corporation from right under my nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.25,0:07:36.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's hear it. Why are you going so far just to test your merits against mine in a match?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}hate{\i0} you. Hate to the point of becoming unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.15,0:07:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You not only stole Kaiba Corporation away from me, but my very {\i1}life{\i0} along with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.16,0:07:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that it's my fault you killed yourself just because I {\i1}beat{\i0} you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're gonna settle things right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.05,0:07:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it must be in the thing you like the best... a Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.99,0:08:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And not only will I utterly destroy you, 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.12,0:08:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you'll crawl back to my feet when you learn how big the gap between us is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright then. I'll be glad to Duel you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.39,0:08:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of who it may be, I accept {\i1}all{\i0} challenges that come my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.61,0:08:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accept this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.06,0:08:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll destroy {\i1}everyone{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}System down. System down.\N Changing to backup generators.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.44,0:08:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tch! How dare you get in my way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.84,0:08:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lock has been undone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.46,0:08:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! Let's get everything ready to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.95,0:09:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come, Seto!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.13,0:09:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card, Distressing Choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.72,0:09:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Distressing Choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.31,0:09:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, being the manager of a company means making decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if those decisions are quite difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.55,0:09:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think that all difficult decisions are {\i1}right{\i0} decisions, you're more foolish than I thought. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.10,0:09:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Difficult Decision has me draw five cards from my deck and show them to my opp-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.24,0:09:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I don't need {\i1}you{\i0} to explain the card to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.25,0:09:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I choose one out of the five cards, and you send the rest to the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.80,0:09:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the card I choose is added to your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Show me your cards already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems I made the right choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.66,0:09:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, take a close look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the five cards I have chosen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?! Those cards...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exodia... is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.11,0:10:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a serious face you've got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.95,0:10:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that you thought I would challenge you to a Duel without doing my research?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.21,0:10:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.88,0:10:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have thoroughly analyzed your deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.43,0:10:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Duel that you\N lost miserably in as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.36,0:10:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.74,0:10:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Exodia, you said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light of Hellfire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.29,0:10:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Exodo Flame!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.11,0:11:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filthy scum...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.70,0:11:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think I'm the kind of man that would lose to the same thing more than once?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just choose already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what's going on here...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.78,0:11:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Exodia is the ultimate card that grants one instant victory the moment he collects all five cards in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.96,0:11:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So why would he want to send them to the Graveyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.72,0:11:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on and choose already, Seto.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.98,0:11:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quick judgment is also an important trait for decision making.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.04,0:11:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.92,0:11:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I shall send the other remaining cards to the Graveyard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.36,0:11:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then place a Monster in Defense Position.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What could he be planning...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:11:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.19,0:12:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}System successfully recovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.12,0:12:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. This time for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Missile target: locked on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.02,0:12:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can join them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.04,0:12:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's game over for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:28.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}30 minutes until missile launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.48,0:12:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.24,0:12:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will they follow us in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.33,0:12:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure we'll be okay in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.39,0:12:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! They found us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.10,0:12:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! We've got no choice but to fight them!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}25 minutes until missile launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.85,0:12:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The control room, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.73,0:13:01.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm~? What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.61,0:13:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no clue what's going on here, but it looks damn interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.71,0:13:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}23 minutes until missile launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've been wanting to\N see you so badly, Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.32,0:13:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've been alone here for so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.36,0:13:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I no longer have any use for {\b0}you{\b1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why don't you all give up on leaving and stay here in this world with me as my father suggested?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's more fun than it looks...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.83,0:13:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:14:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't believe you're still saying that!\N You were abandoned by Gozaburo, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That hurts, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you promise me that you'll stop trying to hurt my big brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.42,0:14:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll be happy to ask\N my brother a favor for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.43,0:14:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To get you a new body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.49,0:14:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, we're brothers and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.04,0:14:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man... He's a complete fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.57,0:14:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.03,0:14:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Comradeship...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.07,0:14:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Friendship...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.25,0:14:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send all of it flying straight into hell aside those idiots with the missile.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.14,0:14:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}21 minutes until missile launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.11,0:14:49.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the missile...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.99,0:14:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.63,0:14:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos Soldier! Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.47,0:14:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos Blade!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.06,0:15:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Axe Raider!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.70,0:15:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}18 minutes until missile launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.26,0:15:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.30,0:15:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who cares about brotherhood, comradeship or friendship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.25,0:15:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! That guy must have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.59,0:15:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the missile can't be stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place one set card face-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.16,0:15:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Blood Vorse!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.68,0:15:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm not sure what he set...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.10,0:15:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But a bluff won't work against {\b0}me{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.27,0:15:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll destroy any enemy standing in my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.57,0:15:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blood Vorse! Attack his face-down Defense Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.15,0:16:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You set one of the Exodia parts on the field?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.12,0:16:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What the hell is this man plotting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.71,0:16:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.26,0:16:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been awaiting this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.18,0:16:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.19,0:16:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I play a Ritual Magic Card from my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.66,0:16:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Contract with Exodia!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.42,0:16:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Contract with Exodia?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Ritual Magic can only be activated when all five of the Sealed Cards are collected in the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.49,0:16:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the cost of 1000 of my Life Points, I am able to initiate the advent of Exodia Necross!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.05,0:16:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exodia {\i1}Necross{\i0}, you said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.47,0:16:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Seto.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.81,0:16:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see with your very own eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.73,0:16:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Exodia that beat you once before is about to be resurrected to the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.07,0:17:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exodia!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.08,0:17:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?! Nostalgic, is it not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.04,0:17:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit the jokes! There's no way a weak Monster with only 1800 Attack Points will be able to beat {\i1}me{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.48,0:17:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A {\i1}weak{\i0} Monster, you say...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.24,0:17:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks as if you know absolutely nothing about Exodia to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.29,0:17:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! Exodia Necross attacks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.68,0:17:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You're going to attack my Monster with Exodia Necross even though it has less Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.06,0:18:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why...?! Why wasn't it destroyed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.61,0:18:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exodia Necross is immortal!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.37,0:18:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And its Attack Power go up by 1000 points every time it engages in battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.64,0:18:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0} did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.06,0:18:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exodia Necross continues to increase its Attack Power without enc until it destroys everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.78,0:18:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.33,0:18:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I'll just use an Assassination Attack Combo until I destroy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Spirit Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.23,0:18:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, reverse card open!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.07,0:18:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Trap Card, Burst Breath!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.50,0:18:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Tribute Spirit Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.13,0:18:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All Monsters on the field with Defense Points less than its Attack Power are automatically destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that means, of course, Exodia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.95,0:18:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.04,0:18:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why wasn't the 0 Defense Power Exodia destroyed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.67,0:19:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.18,0:19:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each of the Exodia parts in the Graveyard hide a unique Effect within them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.91,0:19:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sealed Left Leg of Exodia gives it the Effect to be unaffected by any Magic abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.09,0:19:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sealed Right Leg of Exodia gives it the Effect to be unaffected by Trap Cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.65,0:19:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sealed Left Arm of Exodia gives it the ability to not be destroyed by Monster Effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.79,0:19:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Sealed Right Arm of Exodia's Effect increases its Attack Power by 1000 points every time it does battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.89,0:19:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, Exodia the Sealed One protects it from being destroyed in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.07,0:19:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It grants it the Effect of immortality!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.17,0:19:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The pieces of Exodia have Effects like that when in the Graveyard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.15,0:19:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not only is it unaffected by Magic and Trap Cards... it isn't even destroyed by a Monster Effect or in battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.58,0:20:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Exodia Necross... Is there even a way to beat this thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.85,0:20:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exodia Necross is invincible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.27,0:20:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to beat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.12,0:20:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.17,0:20:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I switch Blood Vorse into Defense Position and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.52,0:20:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}10 minutes until missile launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:31.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon the Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.04,0:20:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Rocket Warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.80,0:20:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.97,0:20:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Invincible Mode!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.95,0:20:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can everyone in\N Virtual Domino City hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.63,0:20:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That voice...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.59,0:20:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard! Where are you?!\N Get the {\i1}hell{\i0} out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.18,0:20:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Seto. And you as well, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.11,0:20:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have taken Mokuba's body and am currently in the Real World.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.29,0:21:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Damn you, Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit! So he really tricked us all and went to the Real World all by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.26,0:21:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah, you jerk! Just how low can you go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.52,0:21:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s body back this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my body as well, OOH-OOOH-AHH~!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.99,0:21:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.12,0:21:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have hardly any time here, but I have something to tell all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A missile is targeting us as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.01,0:21:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And once it hits, both the Virtual World...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.61,0:21:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and the fortress\N will vanish without a trace!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.29,0:21:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.02,0:21:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! Why the hell is a missile of all things headed toward this floating mobile fortress?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.83,0:21:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't get out of here right now, this Virtual Space will be blown up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.97,0:21:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's suspicious enough that Noah has Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s body and is in the Real World!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.40,0:21:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But for now, we need to focus on getting out of this fortress!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.66,0:22:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} is trapped in a Duel with his father!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.34,0:22:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and bring Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} back!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.39,0:22:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Escape!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.27,0:22:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.37,0:22:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.25,0:22:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.55,0:22:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.23,0:22:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.59,0:22:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.18,0:22:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.77,0:22:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.51,0:23:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.69,0:23:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.50,0:23:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.25,0:23:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.23,0:23:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
